extends ../../layout

block content
    title= title
    #content-padder 
    #content-real
        .ctrl-panel
            span#toggle-ctrl-panel.glyphicon.glyphicon-menu-left
            p
                | In this example we demonstrate how to perform a search and how to handle the results including the shape of the AdminBoundary
            p
                | Search allows you to perform Geocode (address to position) and reverse geocode (position to address) searches.
            p
                | The polygon will show the next admin level. If the Address is on MatchLevel house number and/or street only a marker  will be shown. Please notice that for ReverseGeocoding the service only supports the postal code area. Search for an address:
            input#geoCode.form-control(type='text' size='25' value='Schwalbach DE' onkeyup='if (event.keyCode == 13) geocode();')
            br
            div
                p(style='float: left;')
                    | Or do for 
                    span#coord 50.1802815,8.474503934
                    br
                    | (Right click on map to change coordinate) a:
                input#reverseGeoCode.btn.btn-default.btn-sm(type='button' value='ReverseGeocode' onclick='reverseGeocode();')
                div
        tr
            td HLP Service releases which are used in this demo:
            td
                #releaseInfoTxt(style='left:0; top:0; z-index: 0;' value='Used Service Releases:/n')
        #mapContainer
    script(src='/javascripts/examples/v3/admin_boundaries.js')
